Photorealistic style: A weathered wooden Russian nesting doll (matryoshka) sits on an old oak judge's desk, partially opened to reveal progressively smaller dolls inside, each painted with different symbols - scales of justice, a gavel, a scroll, a family tree. Afternoon light streams through tall courthouse windows, casting long shadows across scattered legal documents and an antique magnifying glass. The dolls represent layers of abstraction, from the outermost general form to the innermost specific detail. Dust motes float in the warm golden light, and the rich wood grain of the desk shows years of use. Shallow depth of field focuses on the nested dolls while the background courthouse interior softly blurs.
